Peru Stocks: Atacocha, Buenaventura, Southern Copper, Relapasa

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-05-03T21:03:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/peru-stocks-atacocha-buenaventura-southern-copper-relapasa.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The Lima General Index fell for a second day, dropping 0.3
percent to 19,485.14. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index declined
0.8 percent to 2,617.21.  Mining, bank and telecom stocks fell after a presidential
poll published May 1 gave former military rebel Ollanta Humala a
wider lead over Congresswoman Keiko Fujimori than previous
surveys. The sol weakened 0.2 percent to 2.8273 per  U.S. dollar 
at 4 p.m. New York time, from 2.8231 yesterday.  Cia. Minera Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based zinc
and lead producer, dropped 2.2 percent to 88 centimos, and Cia.
de Minas Buenaventura SA (BVN PE), Peru’s biggest precious-
metals producer, declined 1 percent to $40.80.  Southern Copper
Corp. (SCCO)  , Peru’s biggest copper producer, tumbled 3
percent to $35.50.  Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s
Repsol TPF SA, rose 5.2 percent to 1.63 soles, its highest price
in three weeks.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest
financial services company, dropped 0.5 percent to $95.
 Telefonica del Peru SAA (TELEFBC1)  (TELEFBC1 PE), the local unit of
Telefonica SA, fell 2.2 percent to 2.7 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
